A friend from House Kendan guild named Reiss proposed an idea on the EQ gameplay forum to have alliance/council code implemented so that multi guild chat channels could be set up for raids and things where OOC is not good enough. I found the idea to a good one but Gordon Wrinn aka Abashi quickly dismissed it, not sure why but he does not think communication is that bad on multi guild hunts and raids. The initial post by Reiss was good but the thread got flamey at times and perhaps that is one reason Gordon did not give this topic it's due. I reposted a new topic with the same idea, coding to allow multiple guilds access to one chat channel for raids. I am hoping this thread will be free of flames and that Gordon will give it a second look. I doubt it but it's worth a shot. Please go take a look at my post there, and respond if you agree or disagree.<br>
